{"lemma":"طالِقُ","slug":"طالِقُ","root":"ط.ل.ق","root_slug":"ط-ل-ق","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ل-ق","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26987"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%90%D9%82%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26987","headword_ar":"طَالِقٌ","root":"Tlq","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not having having her fore shank and her arm bound together:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not having upon her a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiTaAm","text_ar":"خِطَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"halter"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IDrd, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repairing to the water;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miTolaAqN","text_ar":"مِطْلَاقٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Aboo-Nasr, K, TA;) of which latter she pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTaAliyqu","text_ar":"مَطَالِيقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is left a day and a night and then milked:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaAliqu","text_ar":"طَوَالِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTolaAqN","text_ar":"اَطْلَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TalaqapN","text_ar":"طَلَقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which last is expl. by AA as meaning she-camels"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that are milked in the place of pasturing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuluqN","text_ar":"طُلُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence: and for an explanation of the pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaAliqu","text_ar":"طَوَالِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to camels, see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TalaqN","text_ar":"طَلَقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", second sentence. Also (O),"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAliqN","text_ar":"طَالِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAliqapN","text_ar":"طَالِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) signifies A she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which the pastor leaves for himself, not milking her at the water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) the former is expl. by Esh-Sheybánee as meaning one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which the pastor leaves"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with her udder bound"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with her"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SiraAr","text_ar":"صِرَار"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not milking her in the place where she lies down to rest:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the latter signifies, (Lth, O, K,) and the former also, (Lth, O,) a she-camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is set loose among the tribe to pasture where she will in any part of the tract adjacent to their place of alighting"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, O, K, ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn","text_ar":"من"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jinAnihimo","text_ar":"جِنانِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the CK being erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janaAbihimo","text_ar":"جَنَابِهِمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":",])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that has not her fore shank and her arm bound together when she returns in the afternoon"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evening, nor is turned away"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the others"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the place of pasturage:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, O:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAliqN","text_ar":"طَالِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies a she-camel, (S, Msb,) and a ewe, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is set loose,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dismissed, to pasture where she will:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb:) and also as first expl. in this sentence: (S:) it is mentioned by ElFárábee as signifying a ewe"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left to pasture by herself, alone."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAliqN","text_ar":"طَالِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAliqapN","text_ar":"طَالِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K,) the former, without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", used by all, (Msb,) the latter occurring in a verse of El-Aashà, (S, Mgh, * O, Msb,) ending a hemistich, and pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAliqapN","text_ar":"طَالِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, [which cite the verse somewhat differently,]) (tropical:)  A woman ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"divorced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"left to go her way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Mgh, * O, Msb, *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"separated from her husband"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by a sentence of divorce"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, * Mgh, * Mgh, * K, TA:) both mentioned by Akh: (O, TA:) accord. to IAmb, one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAliqN","text_ar":"طَالِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"only, because it applies only to a female: accord. to Lth and IF,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAliqapN","text_ar":"طَالِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAliqapN gadFA","text_ar":"طَالِقَةٌ غَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"divorced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to-morrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and Lth adds that it is thus to accord with its verb,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Talaqato","text_ar":"طَلَقَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": some, however, say that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"is affixed in the verse of El-Aashà by poetic license, to complete the hemistich; but an Arab of the desert, in reciting this verse to As, is related to have said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAliqN","text_ar":"طَالِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which equally completes the hemistich]: and the Basrees hold that the sign of the fem. gender is elided in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAliqN","text_ar":"طَالِقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is a possessive epithet, meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAtu TalaAqK","text_ar":"ذَاتُ طَلَاقٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having divorce"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwojuhN TawaAliqu","text_ar":"اُوْجُهٌ طَوَالِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b4-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layolapN","text_ar":"لَيْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaAliqapN","text_ar":"طَالِقَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layaAlK TawaAliqu","text_ar":"لَيَالٍ طَوَالِقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloqN","text_ar":"طَلْقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter half."}],"source_refs":["TA","IDrd","O","K","S","Lth","Msb","Mgh"]}]}}